<TITLE> New society aims to promote public sector efficiency </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 2 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Society for Public Administration was launched Tuesday, with an eye to leading "professional debate on all critical issues of public administration". "One of the major hindrances in realising public administration's potential has been the absence of an effective mouthpiece," said BAPSA's new president, and senior-most professor at Dhaka University, Prof Mohammad Mohabbat Khan in a stateement. "Public administration (PA) as an academic discipline and professional field is comparatively new in Bangladesh. Though PA as both an academic subject and applied field has tremendous potential to contribute to the development of the country in particular and society in general." "It is hoped that the establishment of BAPSA will fulfil, to a large extent, the long-time demand of public administration scholars and practitioners in Bangladesh," Khan added. The objectives of the are to bring about excellence in PA research and practice, advance theory of public, private, and third sector administration and promote efficiency in the public sector. A question-answer session, at a press conference at Dhaka Reporters' Unity, was conducted by vice-president of the society Prof Nazmul Ahsan Kalimullah, who is also chair of DU's Department of Public Administration
